"You can choose any of two options, <guilabel>Display file name only</"
"guilabel> or <guilabel>Display full file path</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Valida on kahe võimaluse vahel: <guilabel>ainult failinime näitamine</"
"guilabel> või <guilabel>faili täieliku asukoha näitamine</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2576
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Background color"
msgid "Use custom background color"
msgstr "Taustavärv"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2578
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enables <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/colors.html\">choosing the document "
"background color</ulink> (the color around the displayed page). By default, "
"the &Qt; toolkit color is used when this option is unchecked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2583
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open new files in tabs"
msgstr "Uute failide avamine kaartidel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether to open new documents in tabs. The tabs are disabled by default."
msgstr ""
"Võimaldab valida, kas avada uued dokumendid kaartidel. Vaikimisi kaarte ei "
"kasutata."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default shortcuts to switch between tabs are <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>.</"
"keycap></keycombo> (<guilabel>Next tab</guilabel>) and <keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>,</keycap></keycombo> (<guilabel>Previous tab</guilabel>)."
msgstr ""
"Vaikimisi kiirklahvid kaartide vahel liikumiseks on <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>."
"</keycap></keycombo> (<guilabel>Järgmine kaart</guilabel>) ja "
"<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>,</keycap></keycombo> (<guilabel>Eelmine kaart</"
"guilabel>)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2592
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch to existing tab if file is already open"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether &okular; should switch to a tab if the file is already open instead "
"of opening a new tab. This option is enabled by default. Can be toggled only "
"if <guilabel>Open new files in tabs</guilabel> is enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2598
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obey DRM limitations"
msgstr "DRM-i piirangute arvestamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether &okular; should obey <firstterm>DRM</firstterm> (Digital Rights "
"Management) restrictions. DRM limitations are used to make it impossible to "
"perform certain actions with &PDF; documents, such as copying content to the "
"clipboard. Note that in some configurations of &okular;, this option is not "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Kas &okular; arvestab <firstterm>DRM</firstterm>-i (Digital Rights "
"Management) piirangutega või mitte. DRM-i piiranguid kasutatakse selleks, et "
"muuta teatud toimingud &PDF;-dokumentide korral võimatuks, näiteks sisu "
"kopeerimise lõikepuhvrisse. Pane tähele, et &okular;i teatud seadistuste "
"korral ei saa seda valikut kasutada."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2608
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reload document on file change"
msgstr "Dokumendi taaslaadimine faili muutmisel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2610
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether opened files should be automatically checked for changes and "
"updated, if necessary."
msgstr ""
"Kas avatud failide korral tuleks jälgida muudatusi ja neid vajaduse korral "
"uuendada või mitte."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2615
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show backend selection dialog"
msgstr "Taustaprogrammi valimise dialoogi näitamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether &okular; should ask the user which backend to use in case of more "
"than one backend able to open the current file. If unchecked, &okular; will "
"use the backend with the highest priority."
msgstr ""
"Kas &okular; peab kasutajalt küsima, millist taustaprogrammi kasutada, kui "
"antud faili jaoks sobib neid rohkem kui üks. Kui see on märkimata, kasutab "
"&okular; suurema prioriteediga rakendust."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2623
#, no-c-format
msgid "Right to left reading direction"
msgstr "Paremalt vasakule lugemise suund"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether to use right to left reading direction by default for the opened "
"files. Can be useful for <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Right-to-"
"left\">some writing systems</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Kas kasutada avatavate failide puhul vaikimisi paremalt vasakule lugemise "
"suunda. See võib olla abiks <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Right-"
"to-left\">mõningate kirjasüsteemide</ulink> korral."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open in continuous mode by default"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether to use the continuous mode by default. In continuous mode, all pages "
"of the document are shown, and you can smoothly scroll through them. "
"Otherwise, only one page (or one row of pages) is shown at a time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2639
#, no-c-format
msgid "When using Browse Tool, wrap cursor at screen edges"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allows endless scrolling around the entire document with the <link linkend="
"\"menutools\">Browse Tool</link>. If enabled, the mouse cursor will wrap to "
"the opposite end of the screen when it touches the borders while dragging "
"the document. This feature is only supported on X11."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2647
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview columns"
msgstr "Ülevaate veerud"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option represents the number of columns to use in the overview mode."
msgstr "See valik on mõeldud ülevaaterežiimi veergude arvu määramiseks."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2655
#, no-c-format
msgid "Page Up/Down overlap"
msgstr "Page Up/Down jätab näha"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2657
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Here you can define the percentage of the current viewing area that "
#| "should be visible after pressing <keycap>Page Up</keycap>/<keycap>Page "
#| "Down</keycap> keys."
msgid ""
"Here you can define the percentage of the current viewing area that should "
"be visible after pressing &PgUp;/&PgDn; keys."
msgstr ""
"Siin saab määrata protsendina, kui palju aktiivsest vaatealast jääb näha "
"<keycap>Page Up</keycap>/<keycap>Page Down</keycap> klahvi kasutamisel."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2663
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Zoom"
msgstr "Vaikimisi suurendus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2665
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This options specifies the default zoom mode for file which were never "
#| "opened before. For those files which were opened before the previous zoom "
#| "mode is applied."
msgid ""
"This option specifies the default zoom mode for files which were never "
"opened before. For those files which were opened before, the previous zoom "
"mode is applied."
msgstr ""
"See määrab vaikimisi suurenduse failile, mida pole varem arvatud. Varem "
"avatud failide korral kasutatakse viimast suurendustaset."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2675
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Accessibility</title>"
msgstr "<title>Hõlbustus</title>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2678
#, no-c-format
msgid "Draw border around links"
msgstr "Viitade ümber joonistatakse piirded"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2680
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whether to draw a border around links."
msgstr "Kas näidata viitade ümber piirjooni või mitte."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2684
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change colors"
msgstr "Värvide muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2686
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Enables</action> the color changing options."
msgstr "<action>Lülitab sisse</action> värvide muutmise valikud."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color mode"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2692
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<action>Enables</action> the color changing options."
msgid "<action>Defines</action> the color changing mode."
msgstr "<action>Lülitab sisse</action> värvide muutmise valikud."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2695
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invert Colors"
msgstr "Värvid vahetatakse"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Inverts</action> colors on the view, &ie; black objects will be "
"shown white."
msgstr ""
"<action>Vahetab</action> vaates värvid, &ie; musti asju näidatakse valgena "
"ja vastupidi."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2701
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change Paper Color"
msgstr "Paberi värvi muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Changes</action> the paper's color, &ie; the document's background."
msgstr "<action>Muudab</action> paberi värvi, &ie; dokumendi tausta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2704
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The color can be selected using the <guilabel>Paper color</guilabel> swatch "
"below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change Dark &amp; Light Colors"
msgstr "Tumeda ja heleda värvi muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Changes</action> the dark and light color to your preference, that "
"means black will not be rendered as black but as the selected dark color and "
"white will not be rendered as white but as the selected light color."
msgstr ""
"<action>Muudab</action> heledat ja tumedat värvi, mis tähendab, et musta ei "
"näidata mustana, vaid valitud tumeda värvina, samamoodi ka valget."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Convert to Black &amp; White"
msgstr "Teisendamine mustvalgeks"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Converts</action> the document to black and white. You can set the "
"threshold and the contrast. Setting the threshold to a higher value by "
"moving it to the right will result in lighter grays used."
msgstr ""
"<action>Teisendab</action> dokumendi mustvalgeks. Sa saad määrata läve ja "
"kontrasti. Suurem lävi (liigutamine paremale) tähendab heledama halli "
"kasutamist."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invert Lightness"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2727
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Inverts</action> lightness of all colors. Light and dark colors will "
"be swapped, but hue and saturation will not be affected. The Contrast in "
"images will usually be worse than in <guilabel>Invert Luma (sRGB Linear)</"
"guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2733
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invert Luma (sRGB Linear)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Inverts</action> luma of all colors. Light and dark will be swapped, "
"but hue and saturation will not be affected. The Contrast in images is "
"preserved better than in <guilabel>Invert Lightness</guilabel>, but graphics "
"and colorful text markup usually look worse. Uses sRGB luma coefficients, "
"but no gamma correction."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2743
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invert Luma (Symmetric)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Inverts</action> luma of all colors, using symmetric luma "
"coefficients. Light and dark will be swapped, but hue and saturation will "
"not be affected. Very similar to <guilabel>Invert Lightness</guilabel>, but "
"the contrast is in some cases better."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2752
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shift Hue Positive"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Shifts</action> hue of all colors by 120 degrees. Can mitigate some "
"contrast problems in colorful graphics."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2759
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shift Hue Negative"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Shifts</action> hue of all colors by 240 degrees. Can mitigate some "
"contrast problems in colorful graphics."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2766
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure keyboard shortcuts and toolbar actions for the color modes "
"using the corresponding menu items in the <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> menu "
"of the &okular; main window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2770
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text-to-speech engine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Allows you to choose</action> the text-to-speech (<abbrev>TTS</"
"abbrev>) engine to be used by &okular;. The default is <application>speechd</"
"application> <abbrev>TTS</abbrev>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2777
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text-to-speech voice"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2779
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Allows you to choose</action> a voice for the text-to-speech engine "
"to be used by &okular;. You can use all languages and voices depending on "
"the available synthesizers on your platform. On &Linux;, speech-dispatcher "
"is used by default to determine available voices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2787
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Performance</title>"
msgstr "<title>Jõudlus</title>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2790
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable transparency effects"
msgstr "Läbipaistvusefektide lubamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Draw selections and other special graphics using transparency effects. "
"Disable the option to draw them using outline or opaque fill styles and "
"increase speed on selections."
msgstr ""
"Joonistab valikud ja muu spetsiaalgraafika läbipaistvusefekte kasutades. Kui "
"see on märkimata, joonistatakse need kas kontuurina või läbipaistmatut "
"täitmist kasutades, mis kiirendab valikutega manipuleerimise kiirust."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2798
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Memory Usage"
msgid "Memory usage"
msgstr "Mälukasutus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2800
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&okular; can achieve best performance by tuning the memory usage, based on "
"your system and your tastes. The more memory you let it to use, the faster "
"the program will behave. The Default profile is good for every system, but "
"you can prevent &okular; from using more memory than necessary by selecting "
"the Low profile, or let it get the most out of your system using Aggressive. "
"Use Greedy profile to preload all pages without risk of system memory "
"overfull (only 50% of total memory or free memory will be used)."
msgstr ""
"&okular;-iga saavutab parimaid tulemusi, kui häälestad mälukasutuse täpselt "
"oma maitsele ja süsteemi võimalustele vastavaks. Mida rohkem mälu saad "
"kasutada, seda kiiremini rakendus töötab. Vaikeprofiil sobib enam-vähem "
"igale masinale, kuid sul on võimalik takistada &okular;il kasutamast rohkem "
"mälu kui vaja, valides vähese mälukasutuse profiili, või lasta tal kasutada "
"kõike, mida süsteem pakkuda suudab, valides agressiivse mälukasutuse "
"profiili. Ahne profiili kasutamisel laaditakse kõik leheküljed eelnevalt "
"mällu, ilma et riskitaks süsteemset mälu üle koormata (kasutatakse ainult "
"50% kogu- või vabast mälust)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2808
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Rendering"
msgid "Rendering options"
msgstr "Renderdamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2810
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Using this group of options you can improve text and image rendering in "
#| "&okular;. The result depends on the device to display the document. "
#| "<guilabel>Enable Text Antialias</guilabel> and <guilabel>Enable Graphics "
#| "Antialias</guilabel> items can be used to switch on and off <ulink url="
#| "\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spatial_anti-aliasing\">spatial anti-"
#| "aliasing</ulink> of text and images in document, correspondingly. "
#| "<guilabel>Enable Text Hinting</guilabel> item is meant to be a switcher "
#| "for <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Font_hinting\">font "
#| "hinting</ulink>. Antialiasing and hinting change how the documents are "
#| "displayed, you may want to tweak them to your preference."
msgid ""
"Using this group of options you can improve text and image rendering in "
"&okular;. The result depends on the device to display the document. "
"<guilabel>Enable Text Antialias</guilabel> and <guilabel>Enable Graphics "
"Antialias</guilabel> items can be used to switch on and off <ulink url="
"\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spatial_anti-aliasing\">spatial anti-"
"aliasing</ulink> of text and images in document, correspondingly. "
"<guilabel>Enable Text Hinting</guilabel> item is meant to be a switcher for "
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Font_hinting\">font hinting</"
"ulink>. Antialiasing and hinting change how the documents are displayed, you "
"may want to tweak them to your preference."
msgstr ""
"Nende valikute abil saab täiustada teksti ja piltide renderdamist &okular;"
"is. Tulemus sõltub dokumenti kuvavast seadmest. Valikutega <guilabel>Teksti "
"antialiase lubamine</guilabel> ja <guilabel>Graafika antialiase lubamine</"
"guilabel> saab sisse ja välja lülitada vastavalt dokumendi teksti ja piltide "
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spatial_anti-aliasing\">ruumilise "
"antialiase</ulink>. <guilabel>Teksti varjundamise lubamine</guilabel> "
"võimaldab sisse ja välja lülitada <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Font_hinting\">fondi varjundamise</ulink>. Antialias ja varjundamine "
"muudavad dokumentide kuvamist, nii et neid võib siin muuta just oma "
"vajadustest lähtuvalt."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2819
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Presentation</title>"
msgstr "<title>Esitlus</title>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2822
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advance every"
msgstr "Edasiliikumise intervall"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2824
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enables automatic advancing of pages given a time period."
msgstr "Lülitab sisse lehekülgede automaatse vahetamise määratud aja järel."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loop after last page"
msgstr "Viimase lehekülje järel alustatakse uuesti algusest"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When navigating on presentation mode and going past the last page the first "
"page will appear."
msgstr ""
"Esitlusrežiimis liikudes liigutakse selle märkimisel viimasele leheküljele "
"jõudes uuesti esimesele leheküljele."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2834
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Navigating"
msgid "Touch navigation"
msgstr "Liikumine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2836
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allows you to fine-tune touchscreen navigation with tapping in the "
"presentation using the following three possible values:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Tap left/right side to go back/forward</guilabel>: Tapping on the "
"left (right) half of the screen makes the presentation go to the previous "
"(next) slide."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2842
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Tap anywhere to go forward</guilabel> (default): Tapping on the "
"screen makes the presentation go to the next slide, no matter where the "
"screen is being tapped."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2845
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Disabled</guilabel>: Screen tapping does not do anything."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2851
#, no-c-format
msgid "Background color"
msgstr "Taustavärv"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The color that will fill the part of the screen not covered by the page when "
"on presentation mode."
msgstr ""
"Värv, millega täidetakse esitlusrežiimis see osa ekraanist, mida ei täida "
"lehekülg."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2857
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mouse cursor"
msgstr "Hiirekursor"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether the mouse should be always hidden, always shown or hidden after a "
"small time of inactivity."
msgstr ""
"Määrab, kas hiir on alati peidetud, alati nähtaval või peidetakse pärast "
"teatud jõudeolekut."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2863
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show progress indicator"
msgstr "Edenemisnäidiku näitamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2865
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether to show a progress circle that shows the current page and the total "
"number of pages on the upper right corner of the presentation screen every "
"time you change the page."
msgstr ""
"Määrab, kas näidata edenemisnäidikut, mis näitab ülemises paremas nurgas "
"parajasti nähtava lehekülje numbrit ja lehekülgede koguarvu."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2870
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show summary page"
msgstr "Kokkuvõtte näitamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2872
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether to show a summary page at the beginning of the presentation with the "
"title, author and number of pages of the document."
msgstr ""
"Määrab, kas näidata esitluse alguses kokkuvõtet, kus on kirjas dokumendi "
"pealkiri, autor ja lehekülgede arv."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2876
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable transitions"
msgstr "Üleminekute lubamine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this check box to enable or disable transition effects between pages."
msgstr ""
"Selle märkekastiga saab lubada või keelata üleminekuefektid lehekülje "
"vahetamisel."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2882
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default transition"
msgstr "Vaikeüleminek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2884
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The transition effect between page and page if the document does not specify "
"one. Set this to <guilabel>Random Transition</guilabel> to make &okular; "
"randomly choose one of the available effects."
msgstr ""
"Ühelt leheküljelt teisele ülemineku laad, kui seda ei määra dokument ise. "
"Kui valid <guilabel>juhusliku üleminek</guilabel>u, valib &okular; ise "
